===Noun===
'''bunker'''
# A hardened shelter, often buried partly or fully underground, designed to protect the inhabitants from falling bombs or other attacks.
# (Brit.) A large container or bin for storing coal, often built outside in the yard of a house. Now rare, as different types of fuels and energy sources are being used.
# A sand-filled hollow on a golf course.
# In paintball, to constantly fire at an opponent behind an object, even when the opponent cannot be seen, preventing him from firing at other players and trapping him behind the barrier. This can also refer to eliminating an opponent behind cover by rushing the position and firing at extremely close range as the player becomes exposed.

